## What this exposes, actually running it

**Holds together:** the chain traces cleanly — Node ID → Requirements row → Decision ID → Task ID — without
ever needing to edit Concept Architecture or Requirements to get here. `Depends On` did real work: Recharging
Controller's Decision Record genuinely couldn't set its Criteria Used until Battery Source's decision existed,
because "compatibility with the chosen battery" isn't knowable until a battery has actually been chosen.

**A gap this surfaced, not one I already had an answer for:** Recharging Controller's Decision Record needed
to reference Battery Source's Decision Record specifically — not just its Node ID. Right now nothing in the
Decision Records spec formally supports one Decision Record citing another; I wrote "compatibility with the
battery chosen in `DR:PWR.SUPPLY.BATT:001`" straight into the Reason/Criteria prose above because there's
nowhere structured to put it. That's the same problem `Depends On` solved for Requirements, one stage later —
Decision Records may need its own **Depends On Decision** field (distinct from the Requirements-level one)
so a decision can point at the specific decision it relied on, not just the node.

That's a genuine finding from actually running the example, not a hypothetical — worth deciding before this
pattern repeats across more of the tree. Want me to add that field to the Decision Records spec now, or hold
it until more of the tree is run through and you can see how often it actually comes up?
